title: Tilapia Peach Packets
summary: Tilapia Peach Packets is a dairy free main course. One serving contains 634 calories, 72g of protein, and 26g of fat. For $7.26 per serving, this recipe covers 36% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 4. If you have since asparagus season is pretty much over, pepper, giant rainbow cookies, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the salt you could follow this main course with the Apple Turnovers Recipe as a dessert. A couple people made this recipe, and 44 would say it hit the spot. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 45 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 97%. This score is amazing. Similar recipes are Confetti Tilapia Packets, Dilapidated Tilapia Packets, and Tilapia Foil Packets.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir are my top picks for Tilapia. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. You could try Loveblock Pinot Gris. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.6 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 18 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Loveblock Pinot Gris
productMatches.description: Loveblock Pinot Gris is a pale golden with hints of green. The 2013 vintage is a dry style with floral aromas and a hint of ripe pineapple. The palate reveals poached pear and blood orange, and finishes with a touch of citrus, good texture and rich mouth feel.
